# Gitea CICD guideline

## Direct Baseline

- Local OS: Windows
- Workflow dir: `.gitea/workflows`
- Also read before editing deploy flow: `.gitea/workflows/deploy.yml`

## Remote Paths And Targets

- SSH alias: `dev-128`
- Remote host: Synology DSM
- Gitea URL: `http://192.168.6.128:3000`
- Runner container: `gitea-runner-runner-1`
- Runner compose dir: `/volume1/docker/gitea-data/gitea-runner`
- Runner compose file: `/volume1/docker/gitea-data/gitea-runner/compose.yaml`
- Runner config file: `/volume1/docker/gitea-data/gitea-runner/config.yaml`
- Runner data dir: `/volume1/docker/gitea-data/gitea-runner/data`
- Persistent mount: `./data:/data`
- Runner registration file: `/volume1/docker/gitea-data/gitea-runner/data/.runner`
- Cache dir: `/volume1/docker/gitea-data/gitea-runner/data/cache`

## Runner Config Baseline

```yaml
log:
  level: info

runner:
  capacity: 5
  timeout: 3h
  shutdown_timeout: 30s
  labels:
    - "ubuntu-latest:docker://node:24-bullseye"
    - "ubuntu-22.04:docker://node:22-bullseye"
    - "ubuntu-20.04:docker://node:20-bullseye"
    - "node-18:docker://node:18-bullseye"
    - "alpine:docker://node:24-alpine"

cache:
  enabled: true
  dir: "/data/cache"
  host: 192.168.6.128
  port: 8088

container:
  envs:
    - HTTP_PROXY=http://192.168.6.20:7897
    - HTTPS_PROXY=http://192.168.6.20:7897
    - NO_PROXY=localhost,127.0.0.1,::1,192.168.6.0/24,192.168.6.128,host.docker.internal
  force_pull: false
  privileged: false
  network: bridge
  extra_hosts: []
```

## Workflow Baseline

- Cache paths: `.corepack`, `.pnpm-store`
- Package manager: `pnpm@10.29.2`
- pnpm network settings:
  - `network-concurrency=4`
  - `fetch-timeout=120000`
  - `fetch-retries=5`
  - `fetch-retry-mintimeout=10000`
  - `fetch-retry-maxtimeout=60000`

## Gitea Variables

- Secret: `secrets.NAS_SSH_KEY`
- Vars: `vars.NAS_IP`, `vars.NAS_SSH_PORT`, `vars.NAS_SSH_USER`, `vars.NAS_BASE_DIR`
- Keep SSH private key only in `secrets.NAS_SSH_KEY`

## Fixed Conclusions

- Cache endpoint: `http://192.168.6.128:8088`
- Artifact cache API was reachable after runner-side fix
- Cache recovery succeeded with `Linux-pnpm-10-*`
- Main instability was high-concurrency tarball downloads through proxy
- Lower pnpm concurrency improved stability

## Do Not Change Lightly

- Do not remove `8088:8088`
- Do not clear `cache.host`
- Do not set `cache.port` to `0`
- Do not remove runner `/data` mount
- Do not write runner tokens, SSH private keys, or Gitea tokens into repo files
- Do not move `secrets.NAS_SSH_KEY` into `vars`
- Do not introduce new `NAS_*` aliases if existing names still work

## Troubleshooting Order

1. Check `/volume1/docker/gitea-data/gitea-runner/compose.yaml`
2. Check `/volume1/docker/gitea-data/gitea-runner/config.yaml`
3. Confirm container `gitea-runner-runner-1` is running
4. Confirm `8088:8088` is published
5. Confirm `http://192.168.6.128:8088/_apis/artifactcache/cache?...` responds
6. Only then inspect `.gitea/workflows/deploy.yml`

## Operation Notes

- Prefer runner-side diagnosis before changing workflow cache logic
- On Windows, be careful with nested `ssh` + `bash -lc` + heredoc quoting
- If remote bind-mounted files become `root`-owned, repair ownership before cleanup
- Deployment currently clears the old remote directory before copying the new one
